Jan 30 2007	Not One Problem	My husband and I (in an effort to save money) stayed at the Tropicanna on our honeymoon. Sure it wasn't as romantic as some of the other hotels on the strip - but the price was unbeatable, location great, and it allowed us to stay for a few weeks instead of a short vacation. We really didn't have any problems with our stay. We were in the the newer part of the hotel and had a great view from our room. The decor, isn't spectacular. Everything seems to be done in a cheesy tropical motif that looks like it is straight out of the 80s - Vegas style complete with some rooms having mirrors on the ceiling (seriously!). That aside, we found the hotel, overall to be clean, the pool area amazing, and the food to be a good bargain. The pool area seems to be the pride and joy of the establishment and is definitely a place to have a good time. It was even nice for romantic strolls in the evening. There is an older pool on the property and is one to be avoided (it's near the Garden Rooms - which again, avoid - I can see where those rooms would have problems!) Staff was friendly, helpful and there were some awesome bartenders. We found that for most of our stay we were out and about all over Vegas, so really our hotel wasn't that important to us. I could see how someone could be disappointed because it doesn't have the same level of tourist appeal as some of the other themed hotels (Paris, NY NY, Luxor - etc.), and doesn't have the same luxuriousness as the Bellagio, Venitian, or the Wynn. If you are looking for an awesome price and basically a place to crash while you go visit the other touristy spots- this is a good place because it has a great location on the strip - especially with the monorail connecting both ends. If it's your first time to Vegas - you probably won't be impressed and might want to stay at more of a &quot;wow&quot; factor establishment. After the newness of Vegas wears off - this is a good deal place to stay. We would definitely stay at the Trop again if budget was an issue. For a shorter stay we would probably spring for a more expensive hotel, but if we were looking multiple weeks, we would have absolutely no problem staying here again!	
