Aug 28 2006 	Had problems in the beginning but turned out OK.	We had some problems the 1st day, but everything was fine after that. To start things off, it took 1 hr &amp; 15 minutes to check in and this was on a Tuesday night, not a very busy night. Then they didn't have the king bed room we requested in non-smoking so we had to get 2 queens.Our first room was a Garden Room. This is the dilapidated, 50+ yr old section. We had to search for our room in the dark because the lights were out in the hallroom near our room. Once inside, the whole decor in the room looked original and the linens were extremely cheap and 50's style flourescent green. It didn't look all that clean and it certainly wasn't what we were expecting.After numerous complaining, we were moved to the Island Tower, the next best section of the hotel. This turned out to be much better. It was a few decades newer than the Garden Room area and it was clean and perfectly suitable for us.If you're on a budget and want to stay on the Strip, the towers other then the Garden area are a great money saver. They are 2 or 3 times less $$ then neighboring hotels. Just make sure you don't get a Garden Room.	
