Jul 15 2006	Tropicana is still a good choice	I was kind of hesitated after reading so many poor comments about this hotel. But it turned out everything is fine. I heard the garden room is bit noisy and worn out, so I asked at the check in counter if room upgrade is available and see what'll be the extra charge. The man at the check-in counter told me the high tower is not available but he'll pick a quiet room for me. it ended up I had a room on the 3rd floor of the 5000 building with no open view. I didn't mind at all cos the garden rooms are all on 3-storey buildings, it can be quite noisy if you are on lower floor and facing the open area. The room is clean and equipped with all necessary items. No smell, no staine, except the air-con is a little bit noisy at night which is very typical for the old air-con. I didn't try the restaurant there but had a cone of ice-cream at the deli (free with the fun book). The price for food there is not very justified and the setting is not attractive, so don't bother to go there.We went swimming in the morning. The water was a little bit cold. we've also tried the hot water spa. Again not too many people.On the whole, my experience in staying in this hotel is not too bad, at least it has a super location. I stayed 2 night there and 2 nights in the Luxor cos the room rate for Sun and Mon is very high. So we decided to save some by staying at Tropicana for the expensive nights and tried a better hotel during the weekday.	
Jul 14 2006	Fantastic trip	We've stayed in Las Vegas too many times to remember, from the pricy Bellagio and Venetian to plebian Binions, but we had an excellent time this past week at the Tropicana. We were comped on all of our food and drink(nearly $400 worth), got free tickets to shows, won $ at the slots, black jack and poker tables, enjoyed the beautiful pool, ate at Savannah Steak House which was scrumptious, had very good meals at the Calypso Coffee Shop. Every person we encountered on the staff was helpful and pleasant. The room (in the Paradise Tower) was clean and well-stocked. We requested a room close to the elevator and got it. We had easy access to MGM and NYNY for diversions. I would certainly stay there again, and recommend the Trop with no reservation.	
