Feb 17 2006	Good value	I stayed at the tropicana for a week. I paid the extra $10 a night for the island tower and i think it was good value. The room was clean and everything worked. The outdoor pool was closed so i couldn't use it but it looked nice. I had the island buffet breakfast twice and was worth the $11. One morning at about 4am i also went to Calypsos restaurant and had a nice breakfast. The only downside i found was the casino. It is small and looks old, the dealers are not as friendly as other casinos i went to. That being said MGM and New York New York is just across the road. I would stay here again.	
Feb 10 2006	Yes Tired But Great Value	Yes the Trop is getting tired, but that's because the owners can't decide what to do with it...sell it, renovate, implode...??? (right now they are taking reservations only until mid-April)In the meantime, it's a &quot;best kept secret&quot; if you want Vegas without too much glitz and without busting your budget.I admit, I get embarrassed telling my friends (all whom are more Bellagio types) that I stay at the Trop. But I stay there because it is:1. very friendly staff and casino crowd.2. Low minimum tables.3. quiet-er than most of the casinos (but a fun crowd on weekends!)4. Can't beat the rate for a clean, satisfactory room.Tuscani's is the Trop's small, very nice, tastefully appointed Italian restaurant. Only open for dinner. Delicious, well priced. Reservations recommended, I believe. Other than that, I can't comment on the Trop's food; haven't eaten anywhere else there.When I stayed in December, the start of the Las Vegas Marathon was just outside my window, complete with fireworks (at 6 a.m.!!!!) LOL, only in Vegas! I had a great view nightly of the southern Strip - Excalibur, Luxor and Mandalay Bay, all lit up. Gorgeous.Bottom line for me - I like playing there. I've stayed at nicer hotels, but didn't necessarily like the gaming. I like to play with a friendly, fun crowd and friendly dealers, and almost always find them at the Trop!	
