Jun 13 2005	Will stay at the trop. from now on	We visit Vegas twice a year and have stayed at several different hotels on the strip. Last year we stayed at the Trop and it is now our favorite. It is older and not as glamourous as some of the others, But they definately make up for that in service. Our room was spotless. The view was amazing. And we had one of our best Vegas meals at the Savannah steak house. The staff literally bent over backwards to please. The spa was wonderful and I highly recommend the couples massage. The prices on rooms, spa, food etc. can not be beat. There are places with better rooms but the prices are MUCH higher, and I personally don't spend a lot of time in my room and as long as the rooms are clean ( which ours was, very clean) I would gladly take service and value over glamour any day.	
