Feb 6 2005	Great Value	I stayed at the Tropicana December 19-22 2004. I did have some apprehensions about staying here after reading many mixed reviews. Upon entering we had a short wait in line and were upgraded at no cost to a Tower room. The room was large and clean. The room had a king size bed, a couch, large TV and bathroom. The casino itself is small and the change ladies were mean! But we had a great time playing the slots. We joined the Player's Club right away and after 3 days earned 2 tshirts, sweatshirt and a windbreaker. We also used coupons we received to eat in the coffee house since they were open 24 hrs. It was better than I expected. The location is great, at the beginning of the strip with the walkway to MGM right outside the front door. While the Trop doesnt have the glitz and glam of the newer hotels on the Strip, it is a great deal if you there to explore other casinos. We spent most of our trip outside the hotel room any way and it was a great place to just come back to sleep and play slots late at night. I highly recommend this hotel for budget travelers!	
